How can I pay tuition fees?.answer: You can pay tuition fees in several ways // QR CODE – available online and you can complete the payment until 23.00 hours // Cash – go to any branch of Bangkok Bank, Krungthai, Kasikorn, Siam Commercial or Government Savings Bank during the cash‑payment period announced for the semester (for example 25 ถึง 29 April 2565 in the past) and pay before the bank’s closing time // Credit card at the university Treasury – payment accepted until 16.30 hours on the last day of the payment window // Credit‑card online – you can pay up to 23.00 hours // Automatic bank‑deduction – only for students who have signed an agreement with SCB and have sufficient balance, the fee will be deducted automatically // For the current academic year 2568 the payment windows are: // Semester 1 (2025 June – 2025 Oct) – Monday 7 ถึง Friday 11 July 2568 // Semester 2 (2025 Nov – 2026 Mar) – Monday 1 ถึง Friday 5 December 2568 // Summer semester (2026 April – May) – Monday 27 April ถึง Friday 1 May 2569 // Choose any of the above methods within the specified dates and follow the university’s payment instructions.
